full_text: Case 1:20-cr-00330-AJN Document 136 Filed 02/04/21 Page 15 of 27 Ex. J at 252-254. Thus, after repeated objections, Ms. Maxwell asked the examiner to repeat and then rephrase the question; the rephrased question was met with an identical objection; and after the objection the examiner, in an attempt to cure the foundation problem, added, "If you know?" Ms. Maxwell's response to that question—"I don't know what you are talking about"—was entirely appropriate, and could not have been perjurious. 10 DOJ-OGR-00002424
